               <p>735. 
               
                  <persName id="t18000917-148-defend1459" type="defendantName">
                     ANN 
                     BRODERICK
                  <interp inst="t18000917-148-defend1459" type="surname" value="BRODERICK"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18000917-148-defend1459" type="given" value="ANN"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18000917-148-defend1459" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                  </persName>
               
             was indicted for <rs id="t18000917-148-off804" type="offenceDescription">
                     <interp inst="t18000917-148-off804" type="offenceCategory" value="royalOffences"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18000917-148-off804" type="offenceSubcategory" value="coiningOffences"></interp>
               uttering a counterfeit sixpence
            </rs> to one 
               
                  <persName id="t18000917-148-victim1461" type="victimName">
                     Sarah 
                     Palmer
                  <interp inst="t18000917-148-victim1461" type="surname" value="Palmer"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18000917-148-victim1461" type="given" value="Sarah"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18000917-148-victim1461" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                     <join result="offenceVictim" targOrder="Y" targets="t18000917-148-off804 t18000917-148-victim1461"></join>
                  </persName>
               
            , <rs id="t18000917-148-viclabel805" type="occupation">spinster</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18000917-148-victim1461 t18000917-148-viclabel805"></join>, on the <rs id="t18000917-148-cd806" type="crimeDate">10th of September</rs>
                  <join result="offenceCrimeDate" targOrder="Y" targets="t18000917-148-off804 t18000917-148-cd806"></join>, and in a second Count, within ten days after, to wit, on the 17th, for uttering another sixpence to the said Sarah, knowing them to be counterfeit.(The case was opened by Mr. Knowlys.)</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18000917-148-person1462">
                  SARAH 
                  PALMER
               <interp inst="t18000917-148-person1462" type="surname" value="PALMER"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18000917-148-person1462" type="given" value="SARAH"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18000917-148-person1462" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                  </persName>
             sworn. - Examined by Mr. Knowlys. I <rs id="t18000917-148-viclabel807" type="occupation">keep a chandler's shop</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18000917-148-victim1461 t18000917-148-viclabel807"></join>, in <placeName id="t18000917-148-crimeloc808">Little Bell-alley</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18000917-148-crimeloc808" type="placeName" value="Little Bell-alley"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18000917-148-crimeloc808" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18000917-148-off804 t18000917-148-crimeloc808"></join>; I think it was on the 10th of this month, but I cannot be certain, the prisoner came to my shop; the second time she came was the 17th, it was on a Wednesday, both times; she first asked for some bacon, as much as came to five-pence, and then some butter, which came to two-pence halfpenny, making together seven-pence halfpenny; she gave me six-pence to pay for the bacon, and I gave her a penny out of it; she then gave me another six-pence to pay for the butter, I gave her change, and she left the shop; in less than five minutes, she came again, and said, I think I am like a child, I have forgot half my message, I want a small quantity of tea and sugar, she had half an ounce of six shilling green tea, and one pennyworth of moist sugar, and she gave me another six-pence, for which I gave her change; her paying me three sixpences, rather raised my suspicion, I looked at the sixpence, and said, before the woman's face, that I did not think it was a good one; my sister was in the shop, I gave it to her, she differed from me in opinion, and I took it; after she was gone, I went to the door and found it to be a very bad one, the the shop is very dark; I then took the other two to the door, and found them both had likewise; I then put them aside from the rest of my money, and I saw no more of her till the next Wednesday, about half past time nine in the morning, she asked for a threepenny loaf, and half an ounce of tea, which came to five-pence farthing; she then offered me another six-pence, which I took, and sent for Mr. Powell, the constable, and she was taken into custody; that sixpence was also a bad one.</p>
               <p>Cross-examined by Mr. Alley. Q. You take a great many sixpences in the course of a day? - A. No, not many, it is a small shop.</p>
               <p>Q. Had you known the prisoner before? - A. No.</p>
               <p>Q. There were a great many bad shillings and sixpences found upon her, I suppose? - A. No, neither.</p>
               <p>HENRY POWELL sworn. - Examined by Mr. Knowlys. I am a constable; on the 17th of September, I was sent for to take charge of the prisoner, she behaved very well, she desired ever having been in the shop before, (produces the sixpences) I received them from Mrs. Palmer.</p>
               <p>Mr. 
               <persName id="t18000917-148-person1463">
                  William 
                  Parker
               <interp inst="t18000917-148-person1463" type="surname" value="Parker"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18000917-148-person1463" type="given" value="William"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18000917-148-person1463" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
             proved the money to be counterfeit, and Mr. Alley addressed the Jury in behalf of the defendant.</p>
               <p>
                  <rs id="t18000917-148-verdict809" type="verdictDescription">
                     <interp inst="t18000917-148-verdict809" type="verdictCategory" value="guilty"></interp>
               GUILTY
            </rs> on the Second Count.</p>
               <p>
